to the editor re the scourge of guns editorial sept 5 the daily emotional wear and tear caused by 190 million firearms in civilian hands in america is rarely discussed i live in a beautiful part of upstate new york where i hear sporadic gunfire almost every day gun owners discharging rifles automatic handguns and assault weapons out of season claim to be shooting at targets but how is one to know the incessant nearby noise of these weapons is enough to make a normal person more than a bit anxious my neighbors and i commonly ask ourselves where is that gunfire coming from did the shooting die down is it safe to walk the dog now michael blaine jefferson ny sept 5 2000 the writer is a novelist

